  <title translate="true">Tip #61</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Dolphin allows the classification of classes and methods into multiple categories. In addition it also supplies &quot;pseudo&quot; categories, the membership of which is calculated based on certain criteria.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Pseudo-categories are displayed under the * node in the categories pane in the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Browsers</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">. </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">Examples are, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">deprecated, compilation failures </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">and</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true"> subclass responsibility. </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> Try browsing the existing subclasses of </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">VirtualMethodCategory</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to see how to add your own pseudo-categories.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
